üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. Diffie-Hellman is used for:
A. Data encryption
B. Key exchange
C. Hashing
D. Digital signatures

2. Diffie-Hellman allows two parties to:
A. Encrypt files
B. Share secret key over insecure channel
C. Authenticate users
D. Compress data

3. Which type of algorithm is Diffie-Hellman?
A. Symmetric
B. Asymmetric
C. Hash
D. Stream cipher

4. Caesar cipher is a:
A. Modern cipher
B. Public key cipher
C. Substitution cipher
D. Transposition cipher

5. Vernam cipher is also known as:
A. One-Time Pad
B. Caesar cipher
C. DES
D. RSA

6. RC4 is a:
A. Block cipher
B. Hash algorithm
C. Stream cipher
D. Asymmetric cipher

7. Triple DES is also known as:
A. DES3
B. AES
C. RC5
D. Blowfish

8. XOR encryption is based on:
A. Addition
B. Subtraction
C. Logical XOR operation
D. Multiplication

9. Cryptool is used for:
A. Network simulation
B. Cryptographic learning & analysis
C. Database encryption only
D. Virus scanning

10. Which algorithm is asymmetric?
A. AES
B. DES
C. RSA
D. RC4

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Diffie-Hellman does NOT provide:
A. Key exchange
B. Confidentiality of key
C. Authentication
D. Secure key agreement

12. Man-in-the-Middle attack is possible in Diffie-Hellman because:
A. Weak encryption
B. No authentication
C. Short key length
D. Slow algorithm

13. Which cipher uses substitution technique?
A. Caesar
B. XOR
C. DES
D. AES

14. Vernam cipher security depends on:
A. Algorithm complexity
B. Key length equals message length
C. Public key
D. Hashing

15. Which attack tries all possible keys?
A. Replay attack
B. Brute force attack
C. Spoofing
D. Sniffing

16. Triple DES improves security by:
A. Using larger blocks
B. Encrypting data three times
C. Using public keys
D. Using hashing

17. Which algorithm is vulnerable due to short key size?
A. AES
B. RSA-2048
C. DES
D. ECC

18. Cryptool allows visualization of:
A. Network packets
B. Cryptographic processes
C. OS kernel
D. File systems

19. Which attack exploits poor key management?
A. Brute force
B. Side-channel
C. Key compromise
D. DoS

20. Which is a cryptographic issue?
A. Weak keys
B. Poor randomness
C. Implementation flaws
D. All of the above

üî∫ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
