A. Brute force
B. Man-in-the-Middle
C. Replay attack
D. DoS

22. Which mathematical problem is used in Diffie-Hellman?
A. Integer factorization
B. Discrete logarithm
C. Elliptic curve only
D. Hash collision

23. Which cipher provides perfect secrecy?
A. DES
B. AES
C. Vernam
D. Caesar

24. Which attack observes power/timing behavior?
A. Brute force
B. Side-channel attack
C. Replay attack
D. Phishing

25. Weak random number generation mainly affects:
A. Hashing
B. Key generation
C. Encryption speed
D. Storage

26. Which combination is correct?
A. RC4 ‚Üí Block cipher
B. AES ‚Üí Stream cipher
C. DES ‚Üí Symmetric
D. RSA ‚Üí Symmetric

27. Why Triple DES is slower than AES?
A. Larger block size
B. Multiple encryption rounds
C. Asymmetric keys
D. Hashing

28. Which attack targets reused keys?
A. Known plaintext
B. Key reuse attack
C. DoS
D. Traffic analysis

29. In Cryptool, RSA encryption uses:
A. Same key
B. Public & private key pair
C. Hash only
D. Symmetric key

30. CCEE MOST COMMON TRAP in Session 5 is:
A. Diffie-Hellman purpose
B. Attack vs algorithm mapping
C. Symmetric vs asymmetric confusion
D. All of the above

